---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Fixing AMD Driver Crashes" description="Fix AMD driver crashes with driver cleanup, VBS/Hyper-V fixes, and a download script.">
  <article class="post-container">
    <header class="post-header">
      <a class="back-link" href="/blog/">← Back to Blog</a>
      <h1>Fixing AMD Driver Crashes</h1>
      <p class="post-meta">August 24, 2025 | By Dog Expert Tech</p>
    </header>

    <img src="/blog/b1002787/assets/amdtheme.jpg" alt="AMD driver fix" class="post-image" loading="lazy" />

    <div class="post-body">
      <div class="alert-box">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Updating your motherboard BIOS is often the best first step before adjusting drivers.
      </div>

      <p>If your AMD system is freezing, blacking out, or showing driver timeout errors, the next step is a clean driver reinstall and disabling the Windows features that can conflict with AMD GPU drivers.</p>

      <div class="image-row">
        <img src="/blog/b1002787/assets/amd.png" alt="AMD warning" loading="lazy" />
        <img src="/blog/b1002787/assets/amdview.png" alt="AMD driver error" loading="lazy" />
      </div>

      <h2>1. Driver Cleanup & Reinstall</h2>
      <p>Use DDU in Safe Mode to completely remove old GPU drivers. Then install the latest official AMD drivers for your GPU.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/go/HvUTdUi/">Download DDU Here</a></li>
        <li>Run DDU in Safe Mode.</li>
        <li>
          Reinstall the latest stable drivers from the official
          <a href="/go/ADBAMD29/">AMD Support Page</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Disable Hyper-V & VBS</h2>
      <p>Virtualization features such as Hyper-V and Virtualization-Based Security can cause driver instability with AMD GPUs.</p>

      <h2>3. Use the automated fix script</h2>
      <div class="download-card">
        <a class="download-btn" href="/blog/b1002787/assets/disable-hyperv.bat" download>
          📥 Download disable-hyperv.bat
        </a>
        <p>Right-click the downloaded file and choose "Run as Administrator".</p>
      </div>

      <pre><code>@echo off

echo ===========================
echo Hyper-V / VBS Killer Script
echo ===========================

dism /Online /Disable-Feature:Microsoft-Hyper-V-All /NoRestart
dism /Online /Disable-Feature:HypervisorPlatform /NoRestart
dism /Online /Disable-Feature:VirtualMachinePlatform /NoRestart
dism /Online /Disable-Feature:WindowsSubsystemForLinux /NoRestart
dism /Online /Disable-Feature:Windows-Defender-ApplicationGuard /NoRestart

reg add "HKLM\System\CurrentControlSet\Control\DeviceGuard" /v EnableVirtualizationBasedSecurity /t REG_DWORD /d 0 /f
exit /b</code></pre>
    </div>

    <footer class="post-footer">
      <div id="google_translate_element"></div>
      <p>&copy; 2026 Dog Expert Tech</p>
    </footer>
  </article>

  <script type="text/javascript">
    function googleTranslateElementInit() {
      new google.translate.TranslateElement({
